  "text": "The Grafana database migration framework is implemented in pkg/services/sqlstore/migrator/. The core components are:\n\n1. **Migration Runner (migrator.go)**: The Migrator type manages the entire migration process. It tracks executed migrations in the migration_log table, executes migrations in transaction scope with automatic rollback on failure, and supports database locking to prevent concurrent migrations. Key functions include RunMigrations() for the main entry point and InTransaction() for transaction management with rollback handling.\n\n2. **Version Tracking Table**: The MigrationLog type (migrator.go:49-56) defines the migration_log table schema which stores migration_id, SQL, success status, error messages, and timestamps. The table is automatically created via AddCreateMigration().\n\n3. **SQL Dialect Abstraction**: Implemented through the Dialect interface (dialect.go:19-108) with database-specific implementations:\n   - MySQLDialect (mysql_dialect.go): MySQL-specific SQL generation and quoting\n   - PostgresDialect (postgres_dialect.go): PostgreSQL-specific SQL generation\n   - SQLite3 (sqlite_dialect.go): SQLite-specific SQL generation and type mappings\n   Each dialect handles quoting, boolean values, type mappings, index/column checking, and database-specific features.\n\n4. **Migration Types (migrations.go)**: Various migration types support different schema change patterns:\n   - RawSQLMigration: Direct SQL migrations with per-dialect variants\n   - AddColumnMigration: Add columns with existence checking\n   - AddTableMigration: Create new tables\n   - AddIndexMigration: Create indexes\n   - DropTableMigration: Drop tables\n   - RenameColumnMigration: Rename columns (deprecated)\n   - RenameTableMigration: Rename tables (deprecated)\n   - CopyTableDataMigration: Copy data between tables\n   - TableCharsetMigration: Update table charset\n\n5. **Rollback Handling**: The InTransaction() method (migrator.go:415-436) provides transaction management with automatic rollback on error. When a migration fails, sess.Rollback() is called to revert all changes in that transaction. Additionally, SQLite implements retry logic for database locking errors.\n\n6. **Migration Conditions (conditions.go)**: Conditional execution support allows migrations to check if their work has already been done:\n   - IfColumnNotExistsCondition: Only run if column doesn't exist\n   - IfIndexExistsCondition/IfIndexNotExistsCondition: Only run if index exists/doesn't exist\n\n7. **Integration**: The framework is wired into SQLStore (pkg/services/sqlstore/sqlstore.go) which invokes RunMigrations() during database initialization. Specific migrations are registered via OSSMigrations.AddMigration() in pkg/services/sqlstore/migrations/migrations.go."
}

